cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 4 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Each opponent chooses and banishes one of their characters.

Respected, saluted

cards.name: Brawl
cards.cardText:
Banish chosen character with 2 {S} or less.

There are two ways to leave the Snuggly Duckling — the door or the window.

cards.name: Imperial Proclamation
cards.cardText:
CALL TO THE FRONT Whenever one of your characters challenges another character, you pay 1 {I} less for the next character you play this turn.

"By order of the Emperor, one man from every family must serve in the Imperial Army."
—Chi Fu

cards.name: Medallion Weights
cards.cardText: DISCIPLINE AND STRENGTH {E}, 2 {I} — Chosen character gets +2 {S} this turn. Whenever they challenge another character this turn, you may draw a card.

cards.name: The Plank
cards.cardText:
WALK! 2 {I}, Banish this item – Choose one:
• Banish chosen Hero character.
• Ready chosen Villain character. They can't quest for the rest of this turn.

It's a once-in-a-lifetime view.

cards.name: Vitalisphere
cards.cardText: EXTRACT OF RUBY 1 {I}, Banish this item — Chosen character gains Rush and gets +2 {S} this turn. (They can challenge the turn they're played.)

cards.name: Snuggly Duckling - Disreputable Pub
cards.cardText: ROUTINE RUCKUS Whenever a character with 3 {S} or more challenges another character while here, gain 1 lore. If the challenging character has 6 {S} or more, gain 3 lore instead.

cards.name: Training Grounds - Impossible Pillar
cards.cardText: STRENGTH OF MIND 1 {I} — Chosen character here gets +1 {S} this turn.

cards.name: Anna - Braving the Storm
cards.cardText:
I WAS BORN READY If you have another Hero character in play, this character gets +1 {L}.

After talking to Olaf, Anna marched into the unexpected storm to save Kristoff.

cards.name: Anna - True-Hearted
cards.cardText:
LET ME HELP YOU Whenever this character quests, your other Hero characters get +1 {L} this turn.

Make sure you know what's truly important and be willing to fight for it.

cards.name: Ariel - Treasure Collector
cards.cardText:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)
THE GIRL WHO HAS EVERYTHING While you have more items in play than each opponent, this character gets +2 {L}.

cards.name: Aurora - Lore Guardian
cards.cardText:
Shift 2 (You may pay 2 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Aurora.)
PRESERVER Opponents can't choose your items for abilities or effects.
ROYAL INVENTORY {E} one of your items — Look at the top card of your deck and put it on either the top or the bottom of your deck.

cards.name: Aurora - Tranquil Princess
cards.cardText:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

Her music fills the Illuminary's gardens with joy and light.

cards.name: Dang Hu - Talon Chief
cards.cardText:
YOU BETTER TALK FAST Your other Villain characters gain Support. (Whenever they quest, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

You can find villainy in the most unexpected places.

cards.name: Fa Li - Mulan’s Mother
cards.cardText: When far from home, Mulan often thinks of her calming presence.

cards.name: Flounder - Collector’s Companion
cards.cardText:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)
I'M NOT A GUPPY If you have a character named Ariel in play, you pay 1 {I} less to play this character.

"Ariel, Ariel! You won't believe what I found!"

cards.name: Hades - Meticulous Plotter
cards.cardText: "On this cute little plot Ursula tentacles are sold a mile away. That sneaky sea witch… Wait! I can use this thing. While you keep those hateful Illumineers busy, I can carry out my plan."

cards.name: Hans - Noble Scoundrel
cards.cardText:
ROYAL SCHEMES When you play this character, if a Princess or Queen character is in play, gain 1 lore.

Hans was confident he could bring Anna to Ursula-all he needed was something of Kristoff's to lure her in.

cards.name: Iduna - Caring Mother
cards.cardText:
ENDURING LOVE When this character is banished, you may put this card into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

"Come my darling, homeward bound
When all is lost, then all is found."

cards.name: John Silver - Terror of the Realm
cards.cardText: "There are strange things on the edge of the map: sea witches, entangled glimmers, and so on. I'll stick with my ship, thank you very much."

cards.name: Olaf - Carrot Enthusiast
cards.cardText:
Shift: Discard an item card (You may discard an item card to play this on top of one of your characters named Olaf.)
CARROTS ALL AROUND! Whenever he quests, each of your other characters gets +{S} equal to this character's {S} this turn.

cards.name: Olaf - Trusting Companion
cards.cardText:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

"Isn't this Kristoff's hat? If he went this way, he'll be caught in that storm!"

cards.name: Pascal - Inquisitive Pet
cards.cardText:
COLORFUL TACTICS When you play this character, look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

If you want to find something hidden, get someone who's an expert at hiding.

cards.name: Prince Phillip - Gallant Defender
cards.cardText:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)
BEST DEFENSE Whenever one of your characters is chosen for Support, they gain Resist +1 this turn. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

cards.name: Rapunzel - Appreciative Artist
cards.cardText:
PERCEPTIVE PARTNER While you have a character named Pascal in play, this character gains Ward. (Opponents can't choose them except to challenge.)

"Pascal! A new flower for the wall!"

cards.name: Scuttle - Expert on Humans
cards.cardText:
LET ME SEE When you play this character, look at the top 4 cards of your deck. You may reveal an item card and put it into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

"Wow. This is special. This is very, very unusual."

cards.name: Sisu - Wise Friend
cards.cardText: "It may feel impossible, but sometimes, you just have to take the first step, even before you're ready."

cards.name: The Queen - Diviner
cards.cardText: CONSULT THE SPELLBOOK {E} — Look at the top 4 cards of your deck. You may reveal an item card and put it into your hand. If that item costs 3 or less, you may play it for free instead and it enters play exerted. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

cards.name: Transformed Chef - Castle Stove
cards.cardText:
A CULINARY MASTERPIECE When you play this character, remove up to 2 damage from chosen character.

"A good, hot meal will set you right as rain."
- Mrs. Potts

cards.name: Triton - Champion of Atlantica
cards.cardText:
Shift 6 (You may pay 6 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Triton.)
IMPOSING PRESENCE Opposing characters get -1 {S} for each location you have in play.

cards.name: Triton - Discerning King
cards.cardText:
CONSIGN TO THE DEPTHS {E}, Banish one of your items — Gain 3 lore.

"If this is the only way, so be it."

cards.name: Triton - Young Prince
cards.cardText:
SUPERIOR SWIMMER During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)
KEEPER OF ATLANTICA Whenever one of your locations is banished, you may put that card into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

cards.name: Tuk Tuk - Curious Partner
cards.cardText:
"Some say he's easily distracted. They're not wrong..."
-Raya

cards.name: Dig a Little Deeper
cards.cardText:
Sing Together 8 (Any number of your or your teammates' characters with total cost 8 or more may {E} to sing this song for free.)
Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. Put 2 into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

cards.name: Glean
cards.cardText:
Banish chosen item. Its player gains 2 lore.

"Maybe this is just what I need to make my invention work."

cards.name: Seldom All They Seem
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Chosen character gets -3 {S} this turn.

I know you
I walked with you once upon a dream

cards.name: Treasures Untold
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 6 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Return up to 2 item cards from your discard into your hand.

How many wonders can one cavern hold?

cards.name: Field of Ice
cards.cardText: ICY DEFENSE Whenever you play a character, they gain Resist +1 until the start of your next turn. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

cards.name: Great Stone Dragon
cards.cardText:
ASLEEP This item enters play exerted.
AWAKEN {E} — Put a character card from your discard into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

cards.name: Ice Block
cards.cardText:
CHILLY LABOR {E} — Chosen character gets -1 {S} this turn.

Frozen ink can be harvested and processed to many useful ends.

cards.name: Ariel’s Grotto - A Secret Place
cards.cardText: TREASURE TROVE While you have 3 or more items in play, this location gets +2 {L}.

cards.name: Winter Camp - Medical Tent
cards.cardText: HELP THE WOUNDED Whenever a character quests while here, remove up to 2 damage from them. If they're a Hero character, remove up to 4 damage instead.

cards.name: Aladdin - Brave Rescuer
cards.cardText:
Shift: Discard a location card (You may discard a location card to play this on top of one of your characters named Aladdin.)
CRASHING THROUGH Whenever this character quests, you may banish chosen item.

cards.name: Aladdin - Resolute Swordsman
cards.cardText: "How about we get straight to the part where I leave quickly and you scream after me? No? I can't say I didn't give you a chance."

cards.name: Arges - The Cyclops
cards.cardText:
"Looks like you got some big feelings there, buddy—let's stomp 'em out!"
-Hades

cards.name: Ariel - Determined Mermaid
cards.cardText:
I WANT MORE Whenever you play a song, you may draw a card, then choose and discard a card.

Everything she's ever wanted is almost in reach.

cards.name: Ariel - Sonic Warrior
cards.cardText:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Ariel.)
AMPLIFIED VOICE Whenever you play a song, you may pay 2 {I} to deal 3 damage to chosen character.

cards.name: Beast - Thick-Skinned
cards.cardText:
Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)

He's even tougher than he looks.

cards.name: Chi-Fu - Imperial Advisor
cards.cardText:
OVERLY CAUTIOUS While this character has no damage, he gets +2 {L}.

"You, there! Keep that fighting away from here! It is imperative that I write to the Emperor."

cards.name: Chien-Po - Imperial Soldier
cards.cardText: Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)

cards.name: Donald Duck - Buccaneer
cards.cardText:
BOARDING PARTY During your turn, whenever this character banishes a character in a challenge, your other characters get +1 {L} this turn.

Nobody stands a chance against the daring duck of the high seas!

cards.name: Hercules - Beloved Hero
cards.cardText:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)

cards.name: LeFou - Opportunistic Flunky
cards.cardText: I LEARNED FROM THE BEST During your turn, you may play this character for free if an opposing character was banished in a challenge this turn.

cards.name: Li Shang - Imperial Captain
cards.cardText: Immovable as a mountain and fierce as a dragon—the Empire's finest warrior.

cards.name: Ling - Imperial Soldier
cards.cardText:
FULL OF SPIRIT Your Hero characters get +1 {S}.

A good friend is handy in a fight.

cards.name: Luisa Madrigal - Rock of the Family
cards.cardText:
I'M THE STRONG ONE While you have another character in play, this character gets +2 {S}.

There's no way Ursula's creatures are getting to that donkey.

cards.name: Magic Broom - Aerial Cleaner
cards.cardText:
WINGED FOR A DAY During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

It spends its days keeping the treasured glimmers in the Hall of Lorcana sparkling clean.

cards.name: Magic Broom - Brigade Commander
cards.cardText:
Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)

cards.name: Mickey Mouse - Playful Sorcerer
cards.cardText:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Mickey Mouse.)
Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)
SWEEP AWAY When you play this character, deal damage to chosen character equal to the number of Broom characters you have in play.

cards.name: Mickey Mouse - Standard Bearer
cards.cardText:
STAND STRONG When you play this character, chosen character gains Challenger +2 this turn. (They get +2 {S} while challenging.)

He sets the standard for intrepid adventurers everywhere.

cards.name: Mulan - Armored Fighter
cards.cardText: "Maybe what I really wanted was to prove I could do things right, so when I looked in the mirror, I'd see someone worthwhile."

cards.name: Philoctetes - No-Nonsense Instructor
cards.cardText:
YOU GOTTA STAY FOCUSED Your Hero characters gain Challenger +1. (They get +1 {S} while challenging.)

cards.cardText:

cards.cardText:
STEADY GAZE While you have no cards in your hand, characters with cost 4 or less can't challenge this character.

As regal as his namesake and just as powerful.

cards.name: Raya - Unstoppable Force
cards.cardText:
Challenger +2 (While challenging, this character gets +2 {S}.)
Resist +2 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 2.)

cards.name: Yao - Imperial Soldier
cards.cardText:
Challenger +2 (While challenging, this character gets +2 {S}.)

"I'm gonna hit you so hard, it'll make your ancestors dizzy."

cards.name: Avalanche
cards.cardText:
Deal 1 damage to each opposing character. You may banish chosen location.

A little snow never hurt anyone. That big rock, however...

cards.name: I Find ’Em, I Flatten ’Em
cards.cardText:
(A character with cost 4 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Banish all items.

All the most difficult missions are for me, because I am indestructible.

cards.cardText:

cards.name: Triton's Decree
cards.cardText:
Each opponent chooses one of their characters and deals 2 damage to them.

"Ursula's foul creatures are not welcome in my kingdom!"

EXTRACT OF STEEL 1 {I}, Banish this item — Chosen character of yours gains Bodyguard until the start of your next turn. (An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)

cards.cardText: WITHIN RANGE {E}, 1 {I} — Chosen Hero character gains Challenger +2 and Evasive this turn. (They get +2 {S} while challenging. They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

cards.cardText:
BA-BOOM! {E}, 2 {I}, Discard a card — Deal 2 damage to chosen character or location.

"So help me, I'll use the ship's cannons to blast ya all to kingdom come!"
- John Silver
